---

# Data Sources

The project uses publicly available datasets from Transport for Victoria.

| Dataset | Description |
|---|---|
| Accident Dataset | Road crash accident records |
| Vehicle Dataset | Vehicle involvement data |
| Person Dataset | Driver and passenger information |

All datasets are linked using:
```text
ACCIDENT_NO
```

---

# Visualizations

| # | Visualization | Type | Interaction |
|---|---|---|---|
| 1 | Metric Cards | KPI Cards | Updates dynamically |
| 2 | Annual Crashes by Severity | Stacked Bar Chart | Click to cross-filter |
| 3 | Crash Density: Hour × Day | Heatmap | Tooltip interaction |
| 4 | Speed Zone vs Fatality Rate | Scatter/Bubble Plot | Hover interaction |
| 5 | Crashes by Age Group | Donut Chart | Click to filter funnel |
| 6 | Severity Funnel | Funnel Chart | Linked to donut |
| 7 | Crash Volume by Vehicle Type | Multi-Line Chart | Toggle series |

---

# Cross-Chart Interactions

## Stacked Bar ↔ Dashboard
Clicking a year in the stacked bar chart filters:
- Heatmap
- Scatter plot
- Donut chart
- Funnel chart
- Line chart
- KPI cards

Clicking again resets the dashboard.

---

## Donut ↔ Funnel
Selecting an age group in the donut chart dynamically filters the severity funnel chart.

---

# Application Architecture

```text
loadData()
├── initFilters()
├── applyFilters()
├── applyPersonFilter()
├── applyVehicleFilter()
└── updateAll()
    ├── drawMetricCards()
    ├── drawStackedBar()
    ├── drawHeatmap()
    ├── drawScatter()
    ├── drawDonut()
    ├── drawFunnel()
    └── drawLine()
```

Each visualization function:
- Accepts filtered data
- Re-renders dynamically
- Uses D3 enter/update/exit pattern
- Supports animations and transitions

---

# Installation & Setup

## 1. Clone the Repository

```bash
git clone <repository-url>
cd f21dv_gp_dubai_10
```

---

# 2. Install Python Dependencies

```bash
pip install pandas
```

---

# 3. Preprocess the Data

Run the preprocessing script once to generate cleaned datasets.

```bash
python scripts/preprocess.py
```

This generates:
- `processed_accidents.csv`
- `processed_persons.csv`
- `processed_vehicles.csv`

---

# 4. Run a Local Server

```bash
python -m http.server 8000
```

Open the application in your browser:

```text
http://localhost:8000
```

---

# Design Considerations

## Performance
- Preprocessed datasets reduce browser workload
- Efficient filtering pipeline
- Lightweight frontend without frameworks

## Usability
- Interactive filtering
- Responsive visual feedback
- Clear visual hierarchy
- Dark theme interface

## Scalability
- Modular chart functions
- Reusable filtering logic
- Separation between preprocessing and visualization layers

